1.Trend of Total FDI in India¶

In [7]:
years = df.columns[1:]
total_fdi = df[years].sum(axis=0)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(years, total_fdi)

for i, (year, fdi) in enumerate(zip(years, total_fdi)):
    plt.text(year, fdi, f'{fdi:.2f}', ha='right', va='bottom', fontsize=8)
    
plt.xlabel('Financial Year')
plt.ylabel('Total FDI (in millions)')
plt.title('Trend of Total FDI in India')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

2. Identify the three sectors with the highest values in the most recent year (2014-15)¶

In [8]:
recent_year_data = df[['Sector', '2014-15']].dropna()

recent_year_data = recent_year_data.sort_values(by='2014-15', ascending=False)

top_three_sectors = recent_year_data.head(3)

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
bars = plt.bar(top_three_sectors['Sector'], top_three_sectors['2014-15'], color='skyblue')

for bar in bars:
    yval = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, yval, round(yval, 2), va='bottom', ha='center')

plt.title('Top Three Sectors with Highest Values in 2014-15')
plt.xlabel('Sector')
plt.ylabel('Value')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

3.Sector with Highest FDI Inflow Each Year¶

In [9]:
years = df.columns[1:]
highest_fdi_sectors = {}

for year in years:
    highest_fdi_sector = df.loc[df[year] == df[year].max(), 'Sector'].values[0]
    highest_fdi_value = df[year].max()

    highest_fdi_sectors[year] = (highest_fdi_sector, highest_fdi_value)
    
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20,20))
bar_positions = range(len(years))
bar_height = 0.5
ax.barh(bar_positions, [value[1] for value in highest_fdi_sectors.values()], align='center', height=bar_height)
ax.set_yticks(bar_positions)
ax.set_yticklabels(years)
ax.set_ylabel('Financial Year',fontsize=35)
ax.set_xlabel('Highest FDI Inflow (in millions)',fontsize=30)
ax.set_title('Sector with Highest FDI Inflow Each Year',fontsize=30)
plt.xticks(fontsize=25)
plt.yticks(fontsize=25)

for i, (year, (sector, fdi_value)) in enumerate(highest_fdi_sectors.items()):
    text_y = bar_positions[i]
    ax.text(fdi_value + 100, text_y, f"{sector[:30]}\n{sector[30:]}", ha='left', va='center', fontsize=17)

plt.show()

4.The percentage change in the "Construction Development: Townships, housing, ...¶

In [10]:
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()
construction_data = df[df['Sector'].str.contains('Construction Development', case=False, na=False)]
construction_data = construction_data.groupby('Sector').sum()
construction_data = construction_data.T
construction_data.columns = ['Construction Development']

top_8_years = construction_data.nlargest(8, 'Construction Development')

labels = top_8_years.index
sizes = top_8_years['Construction Development']

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 10))
wedges, texts, autotexts = ax.pie(sizes, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=140, colors=plt.cm.Paired.colors)
ax.legend(wedges, labels, title="Years", loc="center left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
plt.title('Top 8 Years for Construction Development: Townships, Housing Sector Value Distribution')
plt.axis('equal') 

plt.show()

5. Mining sector's value changed over the years¶

In [11]:
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()

mining_data = df[df['Sector'].str.contains('Mining', case=False, na=False)].copy()
mining_data = mining_data.groupby('Sector').sum().T
mining_data.columns = ['Value']

years = np.arange(len(mining_data))
values = mining_data['Value'].values
coefficients = np.polyfit(years, values, 1)
trend = np.polyval(coefficients, years)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(data=mining_data, x=mining_data.index, y='Value', marker='o', label='Actual')
plt.plot(mining_data.index, trend, label='Trend', linestyle='--', color='red')

for x, y in zip(mining_data.index, mining_data['Value']):
    plt.text(x, y, f'{y:.2f}', ha='right', va='bottom', fontsize=8)

plt.title('Yearly Values for Mining Sector with Trend Line')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Value')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

8.Compare the values of the "Power" and "Non-Conventional Energy" sectors across the years.¶

In [14]:
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()
power_data = df[df['Sector'].str.contains('Power', case=False, na=False)]
nce_data = df[df['Sector'].str.contains('Non-Conventional Energy', case=False, na=False)]
power_data = power_data.groupby('Sector').sum()
nce_data = nce_data.groupby('Sector').sum()
power_data = power_data.T
nce_data = nce_data.T
power_data.columns = ['Power']
nce_data.columns = ['Non-Conventional Energy']
combined_data = pd.concat([power_data, nce_data], axis=1)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(data=combined_data, x=combined_data.index, y='Power', marker='o', label='Power')
sns.lineplot(data=combined_data, x=combined_data.index, y='Non-Conventional Energy', marker='o', label='Non-Conventional Energy')
plt.title('Yearly Values for Power and Non-Conventional Energy Sectors')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Value')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

10. The "Coal Production" sector reach its peak value¶

In [16]:
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()
coal_data = df[df['Sector'].str.contains('Coal Production', case=False, na=False)]
coal_data = coal_data.groupby('Sector').sum()
coal_data = coal_data.T
coal_data.columns = ['Coal Production']

max_value = coal_data['Coal Production'].max()
max_year = coal_data['Coal Production'].idxmax()

print(f"The highest value for 'Coal Production' is {max_value} and it occurred in {max_year}.")

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(data=coal_data, x=coal_data.index, y='Coal Production', marker='o')
plt.scatter(max_year, max_value, color='red')
plt.text(max_year, max_value, f' {max_value}', horizontalalignment='left', size='medium', color='black', weight='semibold')
plt.title('Yearly Values for Coal Production Sector')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Value')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

The highest value for 'Coal Production' is 14.08 and it occurred in 2007-08.
